  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Coffee might stimulate bowel movement and thus overcome obstipation in intensive care unit
      (ICU) patients.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      Critically ill patients requiring ventilator support frequently suffer from obstipation. We
      hypothesize that coffee, administered either orally or rectally, might stimulate bowel
      movement.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
